# SEQUENCE 09 — THE QUESTIONS OF TRUTH

/* TRACE: FU-050 | SC-145 */

EXT. VANJI — ARRIVAL ROAD — DAY #60#

Manimekalai enters a city where knowledge itself has become a public space.

Travellers, teachers, merchants and seekers gather.

She does not arrive to defeat anyone.

She arrives to understand.

/* TRACE: FU-051 | SC-146 */

INT. VANJI — ASSEMBLY SPACE — DAY #61#

Different schools present their views.

Each speaker is allowed to be intelligent.

The question is not who is defeated.

The question is what each view can explain.

MANIMEKALAI listens.

/* TRACE: FU-052 | SC-147 */

INT. ASSEMBLY SPACE — LATER #62#

A materialist challenges unseen explanations.

TEACHER

What cannot be experienced cannot become knowledge merely because we desire it.

Manimekalai considers the challenge.

MANIMEKALAI

And what of experience that reveals its own limits?

Silence.

The question changes the room.

/* TRACE: FU-053 | SC-148 */

EXT. VANJI STREET — EVENING #63#

Manimekalai walks among ordinary people.

Philosophy leaves the hall.

A merchant argues over a measure of grain.

A mother waits for medicine.

A child asks why people suffer.

The questions are no longer abstract.

/* TRACE: FU-054 | SC-149 */

INT. ARAVANA ADIGAL'S RESTING PLACE — NIGHT #64#

ARAVANA ADIGAL teaches through questions.

ARAVANA ADIGAL

A conclusion reached too quickly can become another form of ignorance.

He places three objects before her.

A lamp.

A sealed vessel.

A footprint.

ARAVANA ADIGAL

What do you know?

MANIMEKALAI

Only what I have properly examined.

/* TRACE: FU-055 | SC-150 */

INT. KANCHI — HUNGERED CITY — DAY #65#

The lesson becomes real.

The city has no shortage of desire.

It has shortage of food, water and organisation.

Manimekalai sees that compassion requires knowledge of systems.

Not only intention.

END SEQUENCE 09